com.aylanetworks.aylasdk

类 AylaSessionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaSessionManager

  • public class AylaSessionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The AylaSessionManager represents an authenticated session with the Ayla Cloud Service. Successfully signing in via AylaLoginManager.signIn(com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.auth.AylaAuthProvider, java.lang.String, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.auth.AylaAuthorization>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) creates an AylaSessionManager with the sessionName provided to AylaLoginManager.signIn(com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.auth.AylaAuthProvider, java.lang.String, com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.auth.AylaAuthorization>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) and may always be obtained by a call to AylaNetworks.getSessionManager(String).

    Applications should register an object to listen for AylaSessionManager events by implementing the AylaSessionManager.SessionManagerListener interface and registering via addListener(SessionManagerListener). Listeners are notified when the AylaSessionManager refreshes the session's authorization token or if the session is closed.

    Sessions are closed (signs out the user) by calling shutDown(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener). Sessions also may be closed without an explicit call to shutDown(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse>, com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.error.ErrorListener) if the service refuses to authenticate a request to refresh the session token.

      • shutDown

        public AylaAPIRequest shutDown(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse> successListener,
                               ErrorListener errorListener)
        Shuts down the current session and logs out the user. If an error occurred when sending the sign-out message to the cloud service, the session will still be closed and the user will need to sign in again.
        参数:
        successListener - Listener to receive the results of the network sign-out call.
        errorListener - Listener to receive an error from the network sign-out call.
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest for this command. While the request to sign out from the server may be canceled, the session will be closed regardless.

      • refreshAuthorization

        public AylaAPIRequest refreshAuthorization(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAuthorization> successListener,
                                           ErrorListener errorListener)
        Refreshes an authorization with the Ayla cloud service. Authorizations have expirations, and need to be refreshed from time to time. The library generally will take care of updating authorization for you. When authorization is refreshed, if a Session is active, the SessionManager will notify listeners of the refresh.
        参数:
        successListener - Listener to receive the results of a successful call
        errorListener - Listener to receive errors in case of failure
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest to refresh the authorization, or null if an error occurred before sending
